g.title: COMMENT_8d3fe00+1
g.text: !> brief Assert tangential velocity boundary conditions
!> param T Current time (s)
!> param NM Mesh number
!> param APPLY_TO_ESTIMATED_VARIABLES Flag indicating that estimated (starred) variables are to be used

g.title: COMMENT_8d55700+1
g.text: Assign local names to variables

g.title: COMMENT_8d54a00+1
g.text: Point to the appropriate velocity field

g.title: COMMENT_8d59760+1
g.text: Loop over all cell edges and determine the appropriate velocity BCs

g.title: COMMENT_8d5cf60+1
g.text: Throw out edges that are completely surrounded by blockages or the exterior of the domain

g.title: COMMENT_8d60e80+1
g.text: Unpack indices for the edge

g.title: COMMENT_8d68720+1
g.text: Get the velocity components at the appropriate cell faces

g.title: COMMENT_8d88c60+1
g.text: Indicate that the velocity gradients in the two orthogonal directions have not been changed yet

g.title: COMMENT_8d89fe0+1
g.text: Loop over all possible orientations of edge and reassign velocity gradients if appropriate

g.title: COMMENT_9146400+1
g.text: Cycle out of the EDGE_LOOP if no tangential gradients have been altered.

g.title: COMMENT_8d8bce0+1
g.text: IOR is the orientation of the wall cells adjacent to the edge

g.title: COMMENT_8d8c520+1
g.text: IS2 is the other coordinate direction besides IOR.

g.title: COMMENT_8d92ca0+1
g.text: Determine Index_Coordinate_Direction
IEC=1, ICD=1 refers to DWDY; ICD=2 refers to DVDZ
IEC=2, ICD=1 refers to DUDZ; ICD=2 refers to DWDX
IEC=3, ICD=1 refers to DVDX; ICD=2 refers to DUDY

g.title: COMMENT_8d93d00+1
g.text: IWM and IWP are the wall cell indices of the boundary on either side of the edge.

g.title: COMMENT_8d9bf80+1
g.text: If both adjacent wall cells are undefined, cycle out of the loop.

g.title: COMMENT_8d9be60+1
g.text: If there is a solid wall separating the two adjacent wall cells, cycle out of the loop.

g.title: COMMENT_8da3680+1
g.text: If only one adjacent wall cell is defined, use its properties.

g.title: COMMENT_8da9a20+1
g.text: If both adjacent wall cells are NULL, cycle out.

g.title: COMMENT_8da7520+1
g.text: Set up synthetic eddy method

g.title: IF_8de18c0
g.text: SYNTHETIC_EDDY_IF_1

g.title: COMMENT_8de1780+1

g.title: COMMENT_8f68d40+1
g.text: Define the appropriate gas and ghost velocity

g.title: COMMENT_8f823a0+1
g.text: Decide whether or not to process edge using data interpolated from another mesh

g.title: COMMENT_8f85a60+1
g.text: Determine appropriate velocity BC by assessing each adjacent wall cell. If the BCs are different on each
side of the edge, choose the one with the specified velocity or velocity gradient, if there is one.
If not, choose the max value of boundary condition index, simply for consistency.

g.text: Empty_912aee0

g.text: Set ghost cell values at edge of computational domain

g.title: COMMENT_8f8cd80+1
g.text: Compute the viscosity by averaging the two adjacent gas cells

g.title: COMMENT_8f93c00+1
g.text: Check for HVAC tangential velocity

g.title: COMMENT_8f963a0+1
g.text: Determine if there is a tangential velocity component

g.title: COMMENT_8fbf260+1
g.text: Choose the appropriate boundary condition to apply

g.title: COMMENT_8fd7840+1
g.text: SLIP_COEF = -1, no slip, VEL_GHOST = 2*VEL_T - VEL_GAS
SLIP_COEF = 0, half slip, VEL_GHOST = VEL_T
SLIP_COEF = 1, free slip, VEL_GHOST = VEL_GAS

g.title: COMMENT_9116e20+1
g.text: If the edge is on an interpolated boundary, and all cells around it are not solid, cycle
